The global Pride theme this year at Sony Music Group (@sonymusic) & The Orchard is “Transcend.” With many dividing factors present in today’s world, we are transcending our individual differences to unite and show our pride together.

We are proud to support our LGBTQ+ teammates and artists around the globe. From our recently-launched multi-tier partnership with LGBTQ+ media advocacy organization @glaad, to our continued support for The Equality Act in partnership with @humanrightscampaign we’re committed to advancing equity and inclusivity for all.
June is Black Music Month. Black music is at the core of all of our favorite music. This month and always, we honor the influence of Black music everywhere.

Cheers to 25 years! ✨ 

In 1997, Richard Gottehrer co-founded a company to provide independent artists the ability to distribute their music to mainstream audiences. What began on Orchard Street in New York City has grown to over 45 offices worldwide. 

Stay tuned for more content and celebrations as we toast The Orchard’s 25th anniversary throughout 2022.

Your friends at The Orchard wish everyone a happy and healthy holiday season. ❄️✨ 

We’ll be closed for winter recess from December 20 through December 31and will reopen on Monday, January 3, 2022 (Recess dates may vary across our global offices).

Music distribution company @the_orchard_ has earned the trust of artists like Bad Bunny — and "no one has invested more in the independent sector."⁠
⁠
In a feature for Billboard's Indie Power Players issue, CEO Brad Navin shares how The Orchard has become the U.S. market leader among all distribution companies.⁠
⁠
“The deals we’ve done over the years have always been very strategic: a specific genre, a specific region of the world, a specific synergy or enhancing the value proposition that’s going to benefit our clients and our reach,” Navin says. “Is there a great operator or a great entrepreneur there that we want to be a part of what we’re doing? That’s where my motivation lies and that’s how we’ve done our deals historically: working with great operators.”⁠
⁠
Read more at the link in bio.

Fresh off receiving major co-signs from the likes of @lilbieber, @hermusicofficial, @moby, and @littlesimz, the Dutch-Sudanese R&B singer-songwriter @gaidaaonthewebs is back in full force with her latest EP, #YARN, out now via The Orchard. ⁠
⁠
The project pulls at the threads of identity, healing, and truth in an emotional odyssey that weaves together the past 5 years of healing, unlearning, and transformation. “YARN” is a deeply personal narrative – tangled, textured, and told in full color. Where Gaidaa’s acclaimed 2020 debut #Overture offered a bright-eyed invitation into her world, “YARN” arrives not with naïveté, but with earned wisdom. It’s a work of weight and warmth – woven with soul, stitched with self-reflection, and presented in Gaidaa’s unmistakable tone: raw, unhurried, and resonant. ⁠
⁠
From #Empath to #Rolling, each song tugs on a different strand of Gaidaa’s experience, eventually weaving something whole from what once felt frayed. There’s a quiet strength in the way she ties loose ends, even as she leaves some threads intentionally dangling. “YARN” is not about perfection. It’s about presence. It’s about being brave enough to unravel and still choose to show up. #Gaidaa

“My world is seen through music.” 🍃

Meet Iolanta (@eye_am_Iolanta) — a remarkable 13-year-old singer/songwriter whose story is as powerful as her voice. After losing her sight at just nine months old and beating cancer by the age of two, she now channels her journey into music that’s raw, resonant, and deeply empowering.

Iolanta is signed to The Orchard-distributed label @justcallmebymynamerecords, an initiative of @dmfmusic where proceeds help fund free music programs for people with disabilities.

On July 25, she’ll join other incredible Just Call Me By My Name artists on stage at @helloinclusionfest — a free music festival at @bethelwoodscenter in honor of Disability Pride Month.

Grab your free tickets through the link in their bio. Come celebrate resilience, talent, and the transformative power of music.
